# Core library

Architecture: [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md).

## Layers

`commands/` → `shared/runtime.js` → `config/store.js` + `plugins/loader.js` → plugin methods.

Commands must not import plugin internals (scraper/resolver) — only `loadPlugin(id)`.

## Do

- Reuse `lib/shared/http.js` and `AppError` from `lib/shared/errors.js`
- Keep source-agnostic logic here; HTML parsing belongs in plugins
- Hook new output formats via `lib/output/registry.js`
- New commands go in `lib/commands/` and wire in `bin/manga-downloader.js`

## Don't

- Hardcode site selectors or URLs in core
- Bypass `validateConfig` / `resolveRuntime` for config loading
- Duplicate naming logic — use `lib/core/naming.js`

## Key modules

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `shared/runtime.js` | Config + plugin resolution, catalog load |
| `download/downloader.js` | Chapter download orchestration |
| `output/finalize.js` | PDF merge after download |
| `config/store.js` | Config normalize/validate/save |
